othpaste.jpg&h=5ad610c7&s={SIZE}\" />"},{"pid":"6d9e0ebacbe85874af943359514918e12cc44056","tid":253508,"uid":26110,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-05-22T15:00:18.000Z","msg":"<blockquote>其實有 當年黑人牙膏個英文係darkie 係之後先改Darlie</blockquote><br />\ngoogle 左<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n多謝提供資訊<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n<br />\nIn 1990, after Colgate-Palmolive acquired Hawley &amp; Hazel, the English name of the toothpaste was changed to &quot;Darlie&quot;, and the image on the packaging was altered to show a racially ambiguous face in a top hat to avoid racial misunderstanding.[2] However, the Chinese name of the brand, &quot;黑人牙膏&quot; (in English, &quot;Black Person Toothpaste&quot;), remains the same, and a Chinese-language advertising campaign reassured customers that &quot;Black Person Toothpaste is still Black Person Toothpaste&quot;"},{"pid":"132b5751343a3365a3d8c59d1b9361e8d8c01161","tid":253508,"uid":26110,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-05-22T15:02:06.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_4ebKDFxiia8/TPfyKmogVdI/AAAAAAAAIn4/UQnLLwPdwHU/s1600/darlie.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=http%3A%2F%2F4.bp.blogspot.com%2F_4ebKDFxiia8%2FTPfyKmogVdI%2FAAAAAAAAIn4%2FUQnLLwPdwHU%2Fs1600%2Fdarlie.jpg&h=9874fa77&s={SIZE}\" />"}]}